oracial identity, mobilization among descendants of escaped slaves, military-civilian competition in the launch program, and international intrigue. Throughout, he illuminates Brazil’s changing politics of inequality and examines how such inequality is made, reproduced, and challenged. How people conceptualize and act on the unequal conditions in which they find themselves, he shows, is as much a cultural and historical matter as a material one. Deftly broadening our understanding of race, technology, development, and political consciousness on local, national, and global levels, Constellations of Inequality paints a portrait of contemporary Brazil that will interest a broad spectrum of readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAlcântara (Brazil)-Race relations. 0aAlcântara (Brazil)-Social conditions. 0aBlacksxLand tenurezBrazilzAlcântara. 0aBlacksxLand tenurezBrazilzAlcântara. 0aBlacks-Land tenure-Brazil-Alcântara. 0aEconomic development projectsxPolitical aspectszBrazilzAlcântara. 0aEconomic development projectsxPolitical aspectszBrazilzAlcântara. 0aEconomic development projects-Political aspects-Brazil-Alcântara. 0aEqualityzBrazilzAlcântara. 0aEqualityzBrazilzAlcântara. 0aEquality-Brazil-Alcântara. 0aLaunch complexes (Astronautics)zBrazilzAlcântara. 0aLaunch complexes (Astronautics)zBrazilzAlcântara. 0aLaunch complexes (Astronautics)-Brazil-Alcântara. 0aQuilomboszBrazilzAlcântaraxGovernment relations. 0aQuilomboszBrazilzAlcântaraxGovernment relations. 0aQuilombos-Brazil-Alcântara-Government relations. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aBrazil.  aBrazilian Space Program.  aConsciousness.  aEthnography.  aInequality.  aPolitics.  aQuilombolas.  aRace.  aTechnoscience.  aUtopia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniver